      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Lizzie Noel was appointed non-executive board member of the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs in May 2018.</p>

<p>Lizzie has over 20 years’ experience of senior roles in both the private and public sectors. She is the chief executive of Hemera Data Science Ltd and formerly, a member of the founding team of education and technology firm, Tribal Group plc, where she was director of communications from start up to annual revenues of £200 million, and from five to 2,000 employees. She has also served as an expert adviser to the Department for Education and as a senior adviser to Boris Johnson in his first term as mayor of London.</p>

<p>She was a non-executive board member of the Ministry of Justice from 2015-18.</p>

</div>
      </section>

